How can I use the `getnotarizationproofs` command to retrieve notarization proofs using the command line?

You can use the `getnotarizationproofs` command to retrieve notarization proofs by running the following command:
```
verus getnotarizationproofs '[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n},...]'
```
Replace the `type`, `evidence`, `proveheight`, and `atheight` fields with the appropriate values for your use case.

Examples:
> verus getnotarizationproofs '[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n}, ...]'
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "getnotarizationproofs", "params": [[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n}, ...]] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
Can I use `curl` to retrieve notarization proofs from a Verus node?

Yes, you can use `curl` to retrieve notarization proofs from a Verus node by sending a JSON-RPC request to the node. Here's an example:
```
curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "getnotarizationproofs", "params": [[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n},...]] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
```
Replace `myusername` with your actual username, and `http://127.0.0.1:27486/` with the URL and port of your Verus node.

Examples:
> verus getnotarizationproofs '[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n}, ...]'
> curl --user myusername --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"curltest", "method": "getnotarizationproofs", "params": [[{"type":"iCwxpRL6h3YeCRtGjgQSsqoKdZCuM4Dxaf", "evidence":{CNotaryEvidence}, "proveheight":n, "atheight":n}, ...]] }' -H 'content-type: text/plain;' http://127.0.0.1:27486/
